headline: J.M. Smucker: Better Q1 But Volume Resilience Remains A Risk
summary: J. M. Smucker faces ongoing margin pressure from tariffs, input costs, and slow growth, despite recent pricing power in coffee. Read why SJM stock is a Sell.

headline: 'We haven't seen the worst of it': Retailers warn tariff impacts are far from over
summary: Tariffs are driving up costs and straining consumers, leaving retailers from Walmart to Best Buy navigating an unpredictable spending environment.

headline: There’s Trouble Brewing In the Grocery Aisle. Coffee Prices Jolt Higher.
summary: Pumpkin spice season has just begun, but coffee sellers say a combination of poor weather in coffee producing regions and the latest tariffs on imported beans are raising prices on the grocery shelf.
